title: For Sale:  Daewoo DR-200 Gas Piston Operated AR Style .223/5.56 DR200
postcontent:
Have not heard back from last person, so it's for sale or trade again.  Nice Daewoo DR-200 .223/5.56 gas piston operated rifle 18" barrel, this one is a Kimber import.  These are awesome and extremely well built rifles and still used as the Korean's battle rifle, just like our fine men and women use the M4.  It is like an AK-47 and AR-15 rolled into one, you get the best of both worlds.  I really like the iron sights on these rifles, but you can pick-up a small rail to attach optics for around $50 +/- or you can get the full rail system for quite a bit more.  Overall, I would say the condition is very nice/excellent, there are some marks here and there on the receiver, you can see them in the pics.  I don't see these listed to often and they seem to be going for $1,000-$1,500 on average, depending on condition.  Comes with 1 Pmag and 2 Thermold, all 30rd. mags, it uses any std. AR mag.

$1,100 cash or will consider good trades.

If wanting to trade, please state what you have and Exactly what you want to do, straight trade, trade +/- cash, another firearm, ammo, optics, etc. either way, so I know the deal.  I do not need anything in trade right now, but will trade if it makes sense on my end.  If you offer something of less value and do not mention adding cash or other to the deal, I will assume you want a straight trade and pass.  Same on your end, if you have something of higher value let me know what you are looking for on top.    

Below I listed a handful I do not have yet and would not mind owning, but also listed are ones I would not mind having more of and will consider if the deal makes sense, so feel free to offer as I like a bit of everything.

FN SCAR 16 and 17 or AR uppers (or completer rifles) in .450 Bushmaster, maybe .50 Beowulf, would like to try H&K USP or prefer larger like the Tactical or Expert models, that's about it.

Semi-auto rifles, AR, AK, Saiga, PSL, FAL, AR-10, AR-15 and variants.

Semi-auto pistols or revolvers in .357 mag & .44 mag.

Maybe bolt-guns in the common calibers, maybe quality higher power range optics.

Maybe ammo in the popular calibers to help make a deal happen, but not going to give retail value as I do not need any.

Ftf in or around Garland area, but I do make trips to Arlington and Lewisville area on occasion.  Must be legal to own a firearm in TX.  Will ship if needed.

postcontent:
The Adcor Defense B.E.A.R. AR-15 Upper Receiver Assembly, chambered in 5.56x45mm NATO,employs a revolutionary truly Free Floating Gas Piston design. Unlike other competing piston driven designs, the Adcor system eliminates any influence the moving piston may have on the barrel's harmonics upon firing, resulting in greater shot-to-shot consistency and increased potential accuracy. The upper features an Integral Quad Rail Free Floating Handguard and innovative Ambidextrous Forward-Mounted, Non-Reciprocating Charging Handle. The Chrome Moly Barrel is button broached and Chrome Linedwith a 1 in 7" twist for use with heavier projectile weights. 

The Gas Piston Operating System is growing in popularity and offers advantages over the AR-15's traditional direct gas impingement design. Primary among them is keeping hot propellant gases and carbon fouling from being dumped directly into the upper receiver upon firing, keeping the action clean, cool and functioning reliably for longer periods with less maintenance. The B.E.A.R. offers a Tool-Free Take Down piston assembly for easy cleaning in the field. Additional features include an adjustable gas regulator for optimum cycling with different ammunition types and/or sound suppressor usage, and a unique polymer Dust Wiper attached to the bolt carrier that protects the ejection port from outside debris when the bolt is in battery. 

Upper comes complete with bolt carrier assembly, side charging handle, and standard charging handle assemblies, and is ready to drop onto any standard AR-15 lower receiver.

This is an absolute one of a kind firearm.  It’s a hybrid between a Ruger Super Blackhawk .44 mag revolver and a Ruger New Vaquero Montado with a smaller XR3 style grip and special serrations found only on the Montado.   The smaller grip makes this gun very unique and perfect for those who want a full size .44 mag ruger, but a much easier to hold grip.

The upper main frame is a Super Blackhawk stainless steel chambered in .44 Magnum with a 4-3/4 barrel and fiberoptic front sight.  The gun also has an after market cylinder pin and wollf spring kit.    

The lower grip frame is a Ruger New Vaquero Montado, also in stainless steel.  The Montado was a special version of the New Vaquero and includes the older style Ruger XR3 grip frame which is about the same size as the Colt SAA and smaller than the current Ruger grip frames found on most Ruger SAA guns.  The two frames mate up perfectly and work wonderfully together.  The gun shoots perfectly great!   Its especially comfortable for anyone with small to medium size hands and feels like holding a much smaller and less powerful gun than it is.  

I might possibly be interested in a trade, but would prefer cash.  If trading, the guns I'm currently interested in now are...

title: For Sale:  Scam spotting 101
postcontent:
Offer look too good to be true? Nice shiny nickel Python for 1/3 normal price or Colt 70 for $400? Simple test:

- Save the picture on your PC
- Open Google image search (www.google.com/images)
- Drag picture into the search box and search
- Find that the $760 Python was sold previously on an auction site for $1500. Very unlikely to now be a "gotta have cash fast to fix my car/dog/girl" real deal.

You can also just right-click the picture, "Copy image URL", and paste that into Goolge (you need to click the little camera image, then paste the URL).

Good deals can be had. Too-good-to-be-true deals generally means you'll be had. Don't be had.

When the scammers stop getting excited "I'll take it! Where do I send the Postal MO???" emails then they'll go away and this will go back to being a reasonable site.

Good luck. We're all counting on you.

title: For Sale:  Marlin XT-22MR, scope, sling, extra mags, FREE ammo and FREE case
location: West Omaha, Millard, La Vista, Omaha, Nebraska
postcontent:
For sale is a Marlin XT-22MR rifle. Included is a Bushnell 4x32 scope with medium profile rings (not the ones that came with the scope -- those sucked), one 4-round magazine (blue), one 7-round magazine (blue), two nickel 7-round magazines, Winchester sling, original manual, and 100 rounds of Armscor 40gr ammo. A brown vinyl/leather case is included. It's old and not pretty, but it's intact and provides good protection. If you want a brand new black nylon case that I have for this rifle, it's an extra $20. The rifle has a fresh cleaning.

I bought this brand new at Guns Unlimited last year. It has about 250 rounds through it: CCI, Fiocchi, Winchester, and Armscor. My friend bought this model rifle from GU about the same time I did, and we took them to the 100-yard outdoor range in Grand Island. Here's one thing we learned after not expecting much from a $225 gun: once these rifles are sighted in at 25 yards, they're sighted in for 50, 75, or 100 yards. There's no bullet drop out to 100. We tried compensating for an expected drop, but after checking the targets we realized the bullets were going exactly where we aimed. In short, these Marlins are ridiculously accurate. They're also extremely light, which is also unexpected, given the slightly thicker barrels that Marlin uses. The adjustable trigger pull is clean and has a crisp break. There are no variances in its consistency, and I have not modified it from its factory settings.

Why am I selling it? Stupid medical expenses.

Nebraska purchase permit required. Here's how the deal will happen: We meet at the Bullet Hole (108th & Harrison) and we each show our driver's licenses and purchase permit cards. We trade our names and purchase permit numbers on index cards, do the exchange, and away we go. This is to protect both of us!

Respond through this site and I'll send you my phone number, or call you ASAP if you provide yours. Since I'm throwing in the ammo and case for free, the price is firm. Don't let the recent irrational increase in the prices of 22WMR ammo scare you away. I'll tell you how to check notifications about the cheapest prices that come up with several retailers every day on the hour. Cabela's participates in this, and I've used it many times to buy ammo when you can't get it in the store and there's no shipping cost. No worries!

Thanks for looking!
